                    "en": "Where should we go ‚ÄĒ to the park or to the beach?",
                    "ua": "Where should we go ‚ÄĒ to the park or to the beach?"
                },
                {
                    "en": "When will you come ‚ÄĒ today or tomorrow?",
                    "ua": ""
                }
            ],
            "note": "ūüďĆ Which is often used to choose between options"
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "7. How to answer alternative questions",
    "sections": [
        {
            "label": "Choose an option",
            "color": "emerald",
            "description": "The answer is one of the proposed options, NOT Yes/No:",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "Q: Coffee or tea? ‚ÄĒ A: Coffee, please.",
                    "ua": "P: Coffee or tea? ‚ÄĒ A: Coffee, please."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Q: Is it black or white? ‚ÄĒ A: It's black.",
                    "ua": "P: Is it black or white? ‚ÄĒ A: It is black."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Q: Do you walk or drive? ‚ÄĒ A: I usually drive.",
                    "ua": "P: Do you walk or drive? ‚ÄĒ A: I usually go."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Reject both",
            "color": "sky",
            "description": "You can reject both options and offer a third:",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "Q: Coffee or tea? ‚ÄĒ A: Neither. Water, please.",
                    "ua": "P: Coffee or tea? ‚ÄĒ A: Neither one nor the other. Water, please."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Q: Are you from Spain or Italy? ‚ÄĒ A: Neither. I'm from France.",
                    "ua": "P: Are you from Spain or Italy? ‚ÄĒ A: No. I'm from France."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Choose both",
            "color": "amber",
            "description": "Sometimes you can choose both:",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "Q: Do you like cats or dogs? ‚ÄĒ A: Both! I love animals.",
                    "ua": "P: Do you like cats or dogs? ‚ÄĒ A: Both! I love animals."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Q: Coffee or tea? ‚ÄĒ A: I like both.",
                    "ua": "P: Coffee or tea? ‚ÄĒ A: I like both."
                }
            ],
            "note": "ūüďĆ Neither ‚ÄĒ neither, Both ‚ÄĒ both"
        }
    ]
}

